etymologies: mid 19th century; earliest use found in Daily Herald & Gazette (Cleveland, Ohio)

definitions: The death of plants or animals as a result of exposure to frost, snow, or extreme cold.

etymologies: late 18th century; earliest use found in Noah Webster (1758–1843), lexicographer

definitions: To kill (a plant or animal) by exposure to frost, snow, or extreme cold (chiefly in passive).
(Of a plant or animal) to die as a result of exposure to frost, snow, or extreme cold.
